story.title: Virtual Date - Episode 1
story.storyDescription: DateApp: Welcome to the Virtual Dating App 🙂
story.creator: web-uploader

messages.text: Welcome to the Virtual Dating App 🙂
Um…Hello?
I’m not sure what to do…my friend said I should download this and give it a try.
She supposedly found her perfect match with this app 🙄
And you’ll be next! ❤️
Uh huh…so, how do I start?
Just tell me what you look for in a guy.
Well, not crazy, for one.
Searching…Searching…Searching…
I found 1,094,453 non-crazy men for you.
How did you do that?
Wait…there are less than 2 million non-crazy men in the world? Out of billions? 😒
Would you like to refine your search?
YES!
What else do you look for?
Um…It’s better if he’s athletic.
Athletic. Got it. I’ll enter it into the dataset.
Wait! But not in a “dumb jock” kind of way.
Refining search to find an athletic, but sensitive guy…
I guess sensitive is a good way to put it.
I found 102,345 men matching your criteria.
How in the world do I choose one from that big of a pool?
Here. I’ll help you refine it even more.
I’ll search for men only in a 25 mile radius and who are a couple years older or younger than you.
I think I’ve found your match 😁
Really?
Yes. His name is Ross and he plays football for Cal Tech. Here’s a picture of him.
Wow. Mr. Muscles.
By searching his Facebook, Twitter, and Instagram, I see he enjoys walking on the beach at sunset and taking his mother out for dinner.
I’m sold! What happens now?
You go on a virtual date 👫
Does that mean I’ll actually talk to him? 😬
Not the real him.
Just a virtual version of him that I create based on what I’ve gathered from the internet.
If you like the projection, then I’ll put you two in contact.
Creepy…but okay, I’m ready. I think.
You have your virtual glasses?
Yep.
Put them on and I’ll do the rest! At any point, you can say “stop date.”
That will end the simulation before the time is up.
Got it.
Initializing virtual date…Creating environment…
Zoey finds herself on a beautiful beach.
Um. Hello.
Hi Zoey.
This is bizarre. You look SO real.
I am real. It’s just you and me enjoying the gorgeous sunset on this enchanting night.
Are you — oh my…you’re crying…
I just shed a tear every time—
Ross chokes up.
Sorry…every time I see the sun leave us.
And with you, so elegant, so intoxicating—
Whoa now. This is not what I had in mind.
What’s that, my dearest?
Oh boy. STOP DATE! Stop please!
Zoey looks around.
She’s back in her dorm room.
Everything’s in its usual place, like she never left.
Did you not like your date?
Nope. He started crying for no reason.
I’m sorry you had an unpleasant experience. Would you like to try again?
Sure. As long as you promise the next one will be better.
I added a new filter to remove candidates who are “too sensitive.”
Is there any other attribute you would like to add?
I love music. Any musicians out there?
Searching…Searching…
Maybe someone with deep lyrics. Like a cross between Ryan Bingham and Nick Jonas.
Searching indie pop musicians…
I think I found you the perfect one this time 😎
His name is Jayden and he is an up-and-coming artist. He’s performing around the nation.
Not sure how I feel about someone who travels all the time.
Here’s a picture.
Oh my…nice tattoos 😍
Would you like to go on a virtual date?
Why not? I’ll give it a try.
Initializing virtual date…Creating environment…
Zoey finds herself in a trendy night club.
You must be Jayden.
That’s me.
So you’re a musician, huh?
Yep.
What?! Sorry. This club is really loud.
I said YEP.
What kind of music do you write?
What do you mean?
Huh? Sorry, can’t hear…
WHY DID YOU ASK ME THAT?
I don’t know…Just making conversation.
You saying you’ve never heard of me?
Can’t say that I have.
You’re kidding, right? Do you even listen to music?
I love music!
You sure about that?
Geez. STOP date!
Welcome back, Zoey.
Can we filter out arrogant this time?
So, you do not like Jayden?
I don’t think we mesh. Although if he needs a pairing, I know the perfect person.
Who? I always take suggestions.
Himself.
That option is not available at the moment.
It was a joke — oh, never mind.
Would you like to try again?
Ugh…okay. One more time.
Anything else you would like me to search for?
Someone who listens well. Who isn’t caught up in himself.
Okay. I’ve got it this time. I promise.
Who?
Don Miller. He is your age and goes to the same college.
Yeah…I know him. And I can tell you now…
Don’t waste a virtual date. It’s a no.
Should I filter out people you know then?
Yes and ex-boyfriends.
Adding your new criteria.
Okay. I’ve got it now.
Who is it?
Willian Sheffield. Honors student. Athlete. Also a Cal Tech student.
I think you’ll really like him.
Picture?
Here you go.
Cute. Okay. Let’s get this over with.
Initializing date…Creating environment…
Zoey finds herself on a bench on the Cal Tech campus.
Nice to meet you.
Nice to meet you as well.
I can’t believe we’ve never run into each other on campus.
It’s a big campus.
I know, but we both know Kari and Rachel and Steve.
No way! Really?!
Yes! I’m sure we’ve seen each other in passing.
Probably hung out together without knowing.
You look beautiful. Hope saying that doesn’t make things weird.
Thank you. It doesn’t.
I’d love to take you on a real date some time.
That would be fine with me only if…
Yes?
You’re not crazy, arrogant, or too sensitive.
Will laughs.
I don’t think I am, but I’ll let you be the judge.
Then I’d love to go on a date with you.
Suddenly, Zoey finds herself back in her dorm room.
This ends the virtual date.
What?! No! It was going so well.
I’m glad to hear that 🙂
It usually takes a few tries. We’re working out the kinks.
Would you like to be connected with Will?
YES! Please!
Here is his information and contact info…
Wait…who’s that in his profile picture?
Marie Steadwell.
Who is that?
His girlfriend.
You hooked me up with somebody that’s already TAKEN?!
You didn’t filter out “in a relationship.”
UGH! I’M SO DONE WITH THIS APP.
I’m sorry your experience—
Zoey deletes the Virtual Dating App.
I’ll try my luck in the real world…
